value.0: "Oh, you come to cast Trip down into the darkened halls of death, I am so sure of it! Please, do not do this thing to me!" Trip's wiry whiskers begin to twitch nervously.
With a yowl of fright, Trip's shade rises up above his torn and ravaged body. His eyes stare with a glassy look as he listens to an inaudible voice. Finally he sighs and looks at you.
"Choices, choices, they are yours to make, so says the new voice! For a voice in my head, it certainly seems to be most persistent. The other voices don't trust this new voice."
"I can be a good helper, really I can. No one moves through the shadows or picks a lock quite like Trip. And forget about traps, I take care of them for you, yes?"
The quivering spirit twitches feverishly. "The others? They will lie to you, yes they will! But heed the words of Trip; trust no one... ever! Except me... I am the exception to the rule."
"But you know this, sorry, sorry. I grovel at the feet of your wisdom and would serve you well."
"Very well, I accept. Oh, wait; you didn't say what your choice was. Please, tell me you will take me with you!"
"Oh, <FirstName>, you are making me very nervous. It would be better for both of us if you would just choose Trip right now."
Trip's soul lets out a piercing screech as it is torn away from its body and off into dark eternity.
"No, no, no! Please, not into the darkness!" Trip scratches and claws to no avail as his spirit is drawn into another plane of existence.

LinkComment.value: Spirit form disappears, body gets up from the ground, a fully healed, level one fighter.

value.0: "Good choice! Always overrule your better judgment if it is good for Trip!"
"I would be proud to do so! You shall not regret your choice!"
"Questions? I can answer questions. I have no fear of words... unless they are mean, cruel words... or loud words... I do not like loud words either. You cannot trust them!"
"Good, good, your questions were starting to frighten me. Now, if you just want to choose me, then we can get on to making you a wealthy <man/woman>."
"Forget the nasty cat thing. She is mean and cruel and would eat me, if she did not know I would give her some kind of disease! Yes, I am a pest to her, so better not to take any chances."
"Do not take the dwarf man either! He hurts the eyes and hides the shadows with his fiery features! And the nymph? Why I am a perversion of nature, and proud of it! She would 'cure' me of myself."
"But you will choose another besides me... I see that now. So choose either of the latter, but let the hungry Jaboli beast rot and die! Then she cannot eat me."
"Help? Yes, Trip will help you! Just bring me back and see what we can do. You can be my champion and I shall be your shadow! I will keep you safe from harm!"
"Have you seen that hideous face? She claims to have her honor to protect and says she would never eat me, but I know the truth."
"Smells like cat, feels like cat, sounds like cat, smack me if it isn't a cat! The only thing stopping her from eating me is my disease."
"Hmm, maybe if she ate me she would turn into a rat! She might make a sexy rat, do you not agree?"
"That is what they say, but at least I'm handsome! I also have it on good authority that I am very charming... for a rat-like creature... but enough about me..."
"What do you mean? Wait, I suppose if I were eaten I wouldn't much care if she was a sexy rat. Let's not talk about this anymore."
"A good point, a very good point! I applaud your wisdom! That is why I enjoy traveling with you; such uncommonly good sense."
"I sneak. Yes, I sneak so well no one ever hears me. I pick a lock, I disable a trap, and I have even picked a pocket or two. Not yours though... never yours."
"But best of all is my ability to find hidden things. Caches of gold, secret doors, and all of these marvelous things are so easy for me to find. Without me you would be a poorer <man/woman>."

"I could be useful... I could... I could... oh, what could I do? Oh, I know, I can find things, yes. I am very good at finding things that no one else can see. You like things, right? Well, of course you do."

"Red things, purple things, old things, new things, gem things, magic things, things that you can really sink your teeth into and maul for a while, rubbing them through the dust and dirt to add the extra flavor..."
Trip nods enthusiastically. "You are correct and it is true, very possibly, indeed. But you will take me anyways, because you want what is best for you, not what is best for Trip!"
"Oh yes, Trip promises such help as you would never believe. Come, you could choose me now and then the suspense would end. I am not a big fan of suspense. Not so much."
"That is the right path for your thoughts, yes! Listen to that voice of reason! It tells you of the times Trip saved your life when the bad shadows come calling. YOU NEED TRIP! That's what it says!"

Trip's spirit slumps a little. "I guess I should have seen that coming. No one likes Trip. I should just go and bash my head in I suppose. Oh wait, I'm already dead. Well, that's a far better light to see it all in."

"Now, maybe you don't want me for my excellent charm, but think of those large explosions that occur when a trap goes off. Think of the locked doors you might need through. Trip can help you with these and more!"
"Nothing! No voices, no my good friend! There are no voices in here!" He taps his head, then whispers, "Shut up, you must not speak so loud. <He/She> might hear you and not pick us."
"I need to speak to the others before I decide."
"I have made a choice."
"I've made a mistake. I can't choose yet."
"I like you better dead than alive. Goodbye."
"I cannot choose you, sorry."
"Against my better judgment, I think I will need your skills."
"I would like you to return to help me."

Comment.value: Spirit form disappears, his real form will meet the PC when he/she leaves the henchman area.

value.0: "I have a few questions for you first."
"That is all my questions."
"What do you think of the others?"
"I have other questions."
"I guess that helps. Somehow."
"Why do you think she will eat you?"
"A sexy rat? There's an image I didn't need!"
"You are very strange."
"I... I don't even know how to answer that."
"If she ate you, you could hardly appreciate a sexy rat!"
"What skills can you offer me, exactly?"
"Tell me more about why I should choose you."
"I think you're better off dead."
"If I choose you, I'll be expecting plenty of treasure!"
"I guess you are good at finding extra treasures."
"You are too strange, Trip. I'm not sure I could stand to have you around much more."
"What other voices are you talking about?"
